Actress Simphiwe Ngema stands outside the Dumi Masilela Theatre in Germiston. JOHANNESBURG - The Germiston Theatre in Ekurhuleni has officially been renamed after late actor Dumi Masilela. The Rhythm City actor Dumi Masilela died after being shot during an attempted hijacking in 2017. READ: 'Rhythm City' actor Dumi Masilela dies Masilela's widow, Simphiwe, shared pictures from the official ceremony which was attended by close family and friends. "For as long as I live, Nations will know of your greatness', she said. For as long as I live, Nations will know of your greatness. #Neverendinglove #eternalcrush @dmasilela A post shared by  Simphiwe Ngema (@simzngema) on Dec 10, 2019 at 8:19am PST